  "title": "Lead Design Engineer (Creo/SolidWorks, Automation/Semiconductor Equipment)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Lead engineering teams to design and develop semiconductor equipment modules, ensuring integration into full machines through structured design reviews, comprehensive documentation, and thorough issue investigations.</li><li>Implement Continuous Improvement Programs (CIP) to extend product lifecycle, enhance competitiveness, and improve gross margins, while ensuring reliability and feasibility through rigorous testing and verification.</li><li>Support Sales by reviewing specifications, evaluating costing, and assisting in product assessments; respond to sales and service enquiries with accurate technical input.</li><li>Ensure product performance on-site, resolve technical field issues across Sorters, Laser Mark, and Scan product families, and deliver effective solutions to maintain customer satisfaction.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree or Master’s in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent.\nAt least 5 years of experience in <strong>automation or semiconductor machine design</strong>.</li><li>Strong technical background in high‑precision, high‑speed semiconductor equipment, with proficiency in <strong>Creo</strong> or<strong> SolidWorks</strong>.</li><li>Proven leadership and project management skills, with the ability to coach, motivate, and solve problems systematically.</li></ul><p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p><p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p><p>EA Licence: 19C9701<br />Registration: R21100996</p>",
